79.9	The_Bonfire_of_the_Vanities	The Bonfire of the Vanities	The Bonfire of the Vanities is a 1987 novel by Tom Wolfe. The story is a drama about ambition, racism, social class, politics, and greed in 1980s New York City and centers on four main characters: WASP bond trader Sherman McCoy, Jewish assistant district attorney Larry Kramer, British expatriate journalist Peter Fallow and black activist the Reverend Reginald Bacon.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/a/aa/Bonfirewolf.jpg/200px-Bonfirewolf.jpg
